Resolution Constraint Notice

This workflow is STRICTLY designed for 720p resolution.

Only the following resolution is supported:
- Width: 720
- Height: 1280

Any other resolution (for example 512, 768, 1024, etc.) will cause
a dimension mismatch error during latent, pose, or video processing.

Reason:
Multiple nodes in this workflow (pose extraction, latent encoding/decoding,
and video stitching) rely on fixed spatial dimensions that are hard-coded
for 720p. Changing the resolution breaks tensor alignment.

 Please make sure:
- Width is set to 720
- Height is set to 1280
- Input video is resized to 720p before processing

If you need other resolutions, this workflow must be reconfigured
at multiple stages (resize, latent scale, pose nodes).

On 2XL and 3XL machines, please set the attention_mode to **sdpa** in the WanVideo Model Loader node.
The default segeattn backend may cause compatibility issues on high-end GPUs.
